This menu define the drawing or printing options:
- either the iso-surfaces of the solution or color zones
- or the gradient solution with arrows
- or the normal fluxes of heat with arrows.

1: CASE NUMBER of SOLUTION
If the problem is   steady, the number of CASE is equal to 1.
If the problem is unsteady, the solution is stored
every n steps of time.
If the number of CASE is 3, then the solution at the 2nd
steps of time will be drawn.
The solution at Time 0 forms the CASE 1.

2: Drawings of TEMPERATURES
may be drawn after as
  1 :  ISOTHERMAL LINES or SURFACES
  2 :  ZONES of ISOTHERMAL COLORS
  3 :  ZONES by CUTTING PLANES X or Y or Z=CTE
  4 :  PROFILES by CUTTING PLANES X or Y or Z=CTE
  5 :  ALONG A LINE DEFINED BY 2 POINTS
  7 :  2D SURFACE(X,Y,TEMPERATURE(X,Y))
  8 :  2D ERROR from TEMPERATURE_EXACTE()
  9 :  PRINTING of TEMPERATURES

3 : Drawings of TEMPERATURE GRADIENTS drawn with ARROWS 
    at integration points

4 : Drawings of HEAT NORMAL FLUXES with ARROWS at interface points
    of FE

5 : Drawings of ERROR ESTIMATORS only in 2D drawn COLORS and ARROWS

7 : Printings of NODES TEMPERATURES for a given case

8 : Printings of TEMPERATURE GRADIENTS for a given case
    at numerical quadrature formula Points of every FE

9 : Printings of HEAT NORMAL FLUXES for a given case
    at some Points of every FE
    and for each boundary (Points in 1d, Lines in 2d, Surface in 3d)
    of the OBJECT

10: Printings of HEAT FLUXES on PLS of the OBJECT
    for each boundary (Points in 1d, Lines in 2d, Surface in 3d)
